page.title: 01Farmed Wetland North Wootton
page.content: An area of flat reclaimed marshland used for farming, to the north of north Wootton. There are many drainage dykes and ditches and a sluice and two large ponds. There are brick farm buildigs, barns, potato and grain stores and farm cottages. The disused railway station as been convereted into a private house and the signal box has been converted for use by the venture scouts. The scouts have their own headquarteres built on the area which was once the railway line. There is an area of common land which is grazed by horses and cattle.
